The paper proposes a new method for detecting iris presentation attacks using photometric stereo, which involves estimating surface normal vectors in the non-occluded portions of the iris region. This method falls under computer vision (cs.CV) as it involves image processing and analysis. Additionally, the paper involves machine learning techniques for binary classification, which could fall under multimedia (cs.MM) or machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the security implications of iris presentation attacks, which could fall under cryptography and security (cs.CR). Finally, the paper discusses the potential applications of the proposed method in biometric authentication systems, which could fall under human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
